            <title>[CASSANDRA-15340] Resource leak in CompressedSequentialWriter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15340</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In CompressedSequentialWriter, we reallocate the &lt;tt&gt;compressed&lt;/tt&gt; buffer if the existing buffer is not large enough. These buffers are usually direct byte buffers, and we don&apos;t explicitly release their memory here, which delays release until the buffer is gc&apos;d&lt;/p&gt;</description>
